results.name: Primes p such that the number of distinct prime divisors of all composite numbers between p and the next prime is 5.
link: Amiram Eldar, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
program: (MAGMA) a:=[]; for k in PrimesInInterval(2,25000) do b:={}; for s in [k..NextPrime(k)-1] do if not IsPrime(s) then b:=b join Set(PrimeDivisors(s)); end if; end for; if #Set(b) eq 5 then  Append(~a,k); end if; end for; a; // _Marius A. Burtea_, Sep 26 2019
